Problem: 
The bracelet that the Q charms are currently designed to fit on has limited length. Clinicians
have also requested a Q charms “lanyard”-style necklace that can be worn as an alternative to the wristband. ​

Aim:
- (1) design an adjustable bracelet extender that can
be used with the current Q charms bracelets​

- (2) design a wearable lanyard that can similarly
have Q charms attached and detached. 

Design Criteria:
- Must work with current Q charms size/dimensions ​
- Should fit at least 6-10 Q charms on each wearable 

Suggestions:
- Make an extender that is easy to adjust for different wrist sizes.​
- Want charms to stay facing "outward" (no flipping/sliding)​
- Try to keep wearables from being bulky

